  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which place serves the best coffee in New Delhi?",
  "response": "New Delhi is a haven for coffee enthusiasts, and several places stand out for their exceptional brews. Here are a few favorites:\n\n1. **Blue Tokai Coffee Roasters**  \n   Known for their freshly roasted, ethically sourced coffee beans, Blue Tokai offers a variety of single-origin coffees and brewing methods. Their cafes in Khas Roa ````````````d, Saket, and Lodhi Colony are popular spots.\n\n2. **Indian Coffee House**  \n   A historic and iconic chain, Indian Coffee House is known for both its coffee and its old-world charm. The Connaught Place branch is a must-visit.\n\n3. **Caf\u00e9 Turtle**  \n   This quaint, eco-friendly caf\u00e9 in Khan Market and Greater Kailash serves excellent coffee alongside a selection of organic and healthy food.\n\n4. **Theobroma**  \n   Known for its baked goods, Theobroma also serves great coffee. Their cappuccinos and espresso-based beverages are particularly popular.\n\n5. **Perch Wine & Coffee Bar**  \n   Located in Khan Market and Vasant Vihar, Perch offers a curated selection of specialty coffees and a cozy ambiance perfect for relaxing.\n\n6. **Third Wave Coffee**  \n   With multiple outlets across the city, Third Wave Coffee is known for its commitment to quality and innovation. Their cold brews and pour-overs are highly recommended.\n\n7. **Kaffe Pot**  \n   Located in Kailash Colony, this hidden gem offers a serene ambiance and expertly brewed coffee, perfect for a quiet escape.\n\nThe \"best\" coffee can be subjective and depends on your preferences, but these spots are widely acclaimed for their quality and unique offerings.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
